# R6 stage0-gcc-4.0.4 byte-identity pins. Checked from $OUTPUT_DIR by `sha256sum -c` (set -e aborts).
#
# !! RECORD-AT-PIN-TIME (amd64) !! No upstream amd64 gcc-4.0.4 fixed point (live-bootstrap is i386).
# Capture AFTER the first green amd64 CS build, paste the real shas below, then re-enable the gate at
# the tail of build.sh.
#
# Canonical byte-identity anchors = the deliverable compiler + the C runtime (paths RELATIVE to
# $OUTPUT_DIR; the exact 4.0.4/<target> path is x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4):
# <sha>  usr/bin/gcc
# <sha>  usr/bin/cpp
# <sha>  usr/libexec/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/cc1
# <sha>  usr/libexec/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/collect2
# <sha>  usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/libgcc.a
# <sha>  usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/crtbegin.o
# <sha>  usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/crtend.o
# <sha>  usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/4.0.4/specs
#
# NB: libgcc.a reproducibility depends on the archiver. If AR=tcc-musl2 -ar leaves nondeterministic
# member timestamps, switch to R5 binutils `ar` (built with --enable-deterministic-archives) before
# pinning. cc1/xgcc embed no __DATE__/__TIME__ (verified for the s4 fixed point); confirm at capture.
